# OnlyTwins Project Context

## Stack
- **Next.js 16** App Router (React 19)
- **Supabase** — Auth, Postgres (RLS), Storage
- **Stripe** — subscriptions, checkout, webhooks
- **RunPod** — ML image/video generation workers
- **Vercel** — hosting, cron jobs (5 scheduled tasks)
- **Tailwind CSS v4**, TypeScript (strict), Framer Motion

## Core Business Flow
1. User subscribes via Stripe checkout
2. User logs in → `/dashboard`
3. User completes onboarding (`/onboarding/consumer` or `/onboarding/creator`)
4. User uploads training photos (`/upload`)
5. User sets generation preferences
6. System generates monthly content batch via RunPod
7. Results appear in `/vault`

## Admin Flow
- Admin users (by email, `ADMIN_OWNER_EMAILS` env var) are detected in `lib/admin.ts`
- `proxy.ts` (middleware) redirects admins from all customer routes → `/admin`
- Admin shell and customer shell must stay completely separate
- Admin routes: `/admin/**`, `/api/admin/**`

## Hard Rules
- Never break billing, auth/session handling, or webhook idempotency
- Never invent schema columns — always inspect current migrations before writing DB code
- Keep one source of truth per domain
- No dead UI or placeholder flows
- No technical language exposed to customers
- Keep admin UX separate from customer UX
- Prefer modifying existing flows over creating parallel ones
- Keep server-side enforcement for auth, billing, and usage

## Key File Locations

### Auth
- `proxy.ts` — middleware (routing, auth gates, admin redirect, security headers)
- `app/login/` — login page
- `app/auth/callback/` — OAuth callback
- `app/logout/` — logout page
- `lib/admin.ts` — `isAdminUser()` — admin detection by email allowlist
- `lib/roles.ts` — user role utilities

### Billing
- `app/api/billing/checkout/` — Stripe checkout session creation
- `app/api/billing/webhook/` — Stripe webhook handler
- `app/api/billing/portal/` — Customer portal
- `lib/stripe.ts` — Stripe client
- `lib/subscriptions.ts` — subscription state machine
- `lib/entitlements.ts` — plan feature entitlements

### Generation
- `lib/customer-generation.ts` — orchestration
- `lib/generation-engine.ts` — core logic
- `lib/generation-jobs.ts` — job state
- `app/api/cron/process-customer-generation/` — daily cron
- `app/api/webhooks/runpod/` — RunPod completion webhook

### Database
- `supabase/migrations/` — 40+ migrations (source of truth)
- `lib/supabase.ts`, `lib/supabase-admin.ts`, `lib/supabase-server.ts` — clients
- `lib/run-migrations.ts` — migration runner

### Lead Scraping / Outreach
- `lib/scrape-aggregators.ts`, `lib/scrape-youtube.ts`, etc.
- `lib/ingest-leads.ts`, `lib/outreach.ts`
- `app/api/cron/daily-lead-scrape/`, `send-outreach/`

## Cron Schedule (Vercel)
| Time (UTC) | Job |
|---|---|
| 8am daily | `/api/cron/daily-lead-scrape` |
| 9am daily | `/api/cron/enqueue-lead-samples` |
| 10am daily | `/api/cron/send-outreach` |
| 12pm daily | `/api/cron/process-customer-generation` |
| Midnight daily | `/api/cron/monthly-customer-generation` |

## Deployment
- GitHub `main` branch → Vercel auto-deploy
- Env vars live in Vercel dashboard (not `.env` files in production)
- After any schema change: run SQL migration in Supabase dashboard
- Prefer idempotent, safe migrations
